The evidence with the title 'GM is again the world's largest automaker - latimes ' says Jan 20, 2012  ... Less than two years after emerging from bankruptcy,General Motors Co.has regained the title of the world's largest automaker. GM's worldwide sales rose 7.6% to 9 million vehicles in 2011. The Detroit manufacturer last held the top spot in 2007 before it was surpassed ByToyota Motor Corp.the next year. 
